works.title: Hjördis Rheinländer
works.comments:
Dagny Andersen played the piano and the harp and had students in both instruments.

Her main instrument eventually was harp which she played in several orchestras. 

When leaving “National Theatre orchestra”, the famous leader, Johan Halvorsen (1864 – 1935) called her the “good spirit of the orchestra”.

There seems to be only 2 compositions published by Dagny Andersen, the score I have a “rheinlender”: «…easy to play and perfect for dancing. » and a march. 
Both published in 1888.

She was married to one of the leading flute-players in the country at the time, Axel Andersen (1864 – 1943).

Dagny Andersen died in 1940.
